<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="41" type="distribution and biology">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Distribution and biology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
Nothing is known about the life history of this species. There are over 100 specimens in collections (INBio, USNM, JBS) and it occurs throughout Costa Rica at altitudes between 1100 m and 2800 m along all slopes. At higher altitudes the specimens are larger (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Sullivan, JB" journalOrPublisher="Journal Lepidopterists' Society" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" pagination="72 - 77" title="Intraspecific body size variation in macrolepidoptera as related to altitude of capture site and seasonal generation." volume="61" year="2008">Sullivan and Miller 2008</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
